{"_id":"GT4QBDk1mSqHmcCc","name":"Fragment of the Red Compass","type":"gift","img":"icons/sundries/misc/compass-brass-red-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.fragment-of-the-red-compass","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You possess the southern (red) piece of the Compass Rose that Helga guarded. This bloodstone needle pulses like a heartbeat and points toward the nearest Compass Rose piece (now north toward the emerald center piece in Smaragd). While carrying this fragment, you sense the life force of creatures within 30 feet—useful for detecting hidden enemies or determining if someone is dying. Once per Scene, activate the fragment to track one specific person you've met: the needle points toward them for one Scene, even through walls. Warning: this piece is stained with centuries of blood magic—carrying it may attract blood-hungry creatures or cause disturbing visions of Helga's victims.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Obtained from Helga (through combat, negotiation, or inheriting after her death)</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Life-sense is passive but overwhelming in crowded areas. Tracking requires you to have previously met the target. Each additional Compass Rose piece you carry increases the burden—GM may call for Fortitude Checks to resist temporal displacement headaches. Henkle desperately wants this piece.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> temporal, navigation, life-sense, artifact</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.fragment-of-the-red-compass","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["temporal","navigation","life-sense","artifact"],"requirements":"Obtained from Helga (through combat, negotiation, or inheriting after her death)","limitations":"Life-sense is passive but overwhelming in crowded areas. Tracking requires you to have previously met the target. Each additional Compass Rose piece you carry increases the burden—GM may call for Fortitude Checks to resist temporal displacement headaches. Henkle desperately wants this piece."},"sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332109,"modifiedTime":1784280332109,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XbPdVtc82w8iYnlW","name":"Infusion of Purity","type":"gift","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-corked-labeled-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.infusion-of-purity","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have learned Wolfgang's secret recipe to break blood magic: **Infusion of Purity** requires burdock root (courage), nettle (protection), hyssop (purification), and **elderberry** (life). When you spend 1 Increment preparing and consuming this infusion, you gain immunity to blood magic for one Scene: Helga cannot control your blood, puppet you if wounded, or drain your life force. Additionally, if Helga is wounded while you have active Infusion in your system and your blood touches her, it acts as poison—negating her Blood Witch regeneration and causing her to age rapidly. This infusion represents nature's power to cleanse corruption. Wolfgang grows these herbs in his secret greenhouse—you must either rescue him or find his hidden garden.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Rescue Wolfgang from blood servitude and learn his recipe, OR discover his hidden greenhouse and decipher his botanical notes</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Requires 1 Increment to prepare and consume. Ingredients must be fresh—dried herbs lose potency. Only works against blood magic, not other supernatural threats. Effect lasts one Scene (30-60 minutes). Elderberry is the rare component—Wolfgang may have limited supply.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> consumable, protection, anti-magic, crafting</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.infusion-of-purity","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["consumable","protection","anti-magic","crafting"],"requirements":"Rescue Wolfgang from blood servitude and learn his recipe, OR discover his hidden greenhouse and decipher his botanical notes","limitations":"Requires 1 Increment to prepare and consume. Ingredients must be fresh—dried herbs lose potency. Only works against blood magic, not other supernatural threats. Effect lasts one Scene (30-60 minutes). Elderberry is the rare component—Wolfgang may have limited supply."},"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332111,"modifiedTime":1784280332111,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hddjeFaOep6cLGNo","name":"Manycorpses' Tragedy","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/death/skull-horned-worn-white.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.manycorpses-tragedy","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You witnessed or learned the tragic story of Manycorpses—two lovers fused by Helga's blood magic into a monstrous form, forced to serve the witch who destroyed them. This knowledge has hardened your resolve against blood magic's corruption and taught you about the power of love even in monstrous forms. Once per scenario, when facing a creature or person transformed by dark magic, you can attempt to reach their humanity: make a Social Check opposed by their Opposition Level. On success, they hesitate for one Exchange (losing their action), or if they were once good, they may actively help you for one Scene before the magic reasserts control. This represents your ability to see the person beneath the monster.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Witness Manycorpses' tragedy, learn their story from servants, OR speak with them and recognize their suffering</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Only works on beings who were once fully human/humane and transformed against their will. Does not work on creatures who chose corruption or were always monstrous. The transformed being suffers greatly when fighting their compulsion—using this gift is merciful but painful for them.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> social, empathy, anti-corruption, monster-humanization</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.manycorpses-tragedy","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["social","empathy","anti-corruption","monster-humanization"],"requirements":"Witness Manycorpses' tragedy, learn their story from servants, OR speak with them and recognize their suffering","limitations":"Only works on beings who were once fully human/humane and transformed against their will. Does not work on creatures who chose corruption or were always monstrous. The transformed being suffers greatly when fighting their compulsion—using this gift is merciful but painful for them."},"sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332111,"modifiedTime":1784280332111,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
